## Analytics for Linux ##

### Overview ###

Analytics for Linux helps you quickly and easily analyse system and application performance metrics in Splunk.

Just configure collectd on your Linux servers to push metrics to your Splunk HTTP Event Collector and into a metrics index.

All dashboards in the app utilize the mstats command to query the Metrics Store (new to Splunk Enterprise 7.0) which enables massive performance improvements, i.e. up to 200x faster queries.

Dashboards include graphs of CPU, Memory, Swap, Load, Disk Usage, Network Interface Utilization, Processes, and nginx & Apache web servers.

### Support ###

This is an open source project, no support provided, please use Splunk Answers for assistance.

